f370 = Feature(code='cf34brd6',level=1,name='spellcasting',description='You have learned to untangle and reshape the fabric of reality in harmony with your wishes and music. Your spells are part of your vast repertoire, magic that you can tune to different situations. See chapter 10 for the general rules of spellcasting and chapter 11 for the bard spell list.\n[h]cantrips[/h]You know two cantrips of your choice from the bard spell list. You learn additional bard cantrips of your choice at higher levels, as shown in the Cantrips column of the Bard table.\n[h]spell slots[/h]The Bard table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level or higher. To cast one of these spells, you must expend a slot of the spell\'s level or higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.\nFor example, if you know the 1st-level spell cure wounds and have a 1st-level and a 2nd-level spell slot available, you can cast cure wounds using either slot.\n[h]spells known of first level and higher[/h]You know four 1st-level bard spells of your choice from the bard spell list.\nThe Spells Known column of the bard table shows when you learn more bard spells of your choice. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots, as shown on the table. For instance, when you reach 3rd level in this class, you can learn one new spell of 1st or 2nd level.\nAdditionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the bard spells you know and replace it with another spell from the bard list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots.\n[h]spellcasting ability[/h]Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your bard spells. Your magic comes from the heart and soul you pour into the performance of your music or oration. You use your charisma whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your charisma modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a bard spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.\n[ul]Spell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Carisma modifier[/li/]Spell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier[/ul]\n[h]ritual casting[/h]You can cast any bard spell you know as a ritual if that spell has the ritual tag.\n[h]spellcasting focus[/h]You can use a musical instrument (see chapter 5, &#8220;Equipment&#8221;) as a spellcasting focus for your bard spells.',type='extra spells',category='class feature')
f371 = Feature(code='cf35brd7',level=1,name='bardic inspiration',description='You can inspire others through stirring words or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6.\nOnce within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the DM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest.\nYour Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d10 at 10th level, and a d12 at 15th level.',type='various',category='class feature')
f372 = Feature(code='cf36brd8',level=2,name='jack of all trades',description='Starting at 2nd level, you can add half your proficiency bonus, rounded down, to any ability check you make that doesn\'t already include your proficiency bonus.',type='enhanced proficiencies',category='class feature')
f373 = Feature(code='cf37brd9',level=2,name='song of rest',description='Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures who hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest by spending one or more Hit Dice, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points.\nThe extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d10 at 13th level, and to 1d12 at 17th level.',type='enhanced hit points',category='class feature')
f374 = Feature(code='cf38brd10',level=3,name='bardic college',description='At 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college of your choice: the College of Lore or the College of Valor, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th and 14th level.',type='class specialty',category='class feature')
f375 = Feature(code='cf39brd11',level=3,name='expertise',description='At 3rd level, choose two of your skill proficiencies. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the chosen proficiencies.\nAt 10th level, you can choose another two skill proficiencies to gain this benefit.',type='enhanced proficiencies',category='class feature')
f376 = Feature(code='cf40brd12',level=4,name='ability score improvement',description='When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.',type='enhanced abilities',category='class feature')
f377 = Feature(code='cf41brd13',level=5,name='font of inspiration',description='Beginning when you reach 5th level, you regain all of your expended uses of Bardic Inspiration when you finish a short or long rest.',type='miscellaneous',category='class feature')
f378 = Feature(code='cf42brd14',level=6,name='counter charm',description='mind-influencing effects. As an action, you can start a performance that lasts until the end of your next turn. During that time, you and any friendly creatures within 30 feet of you have advantage on saving throws against being frightened or charmed. A creature must be able to hear you to gain this benefit. The performance ends early if you are incapacitated or silenced or if you voluntarily end it (no action required).',type='advantage/resistance',category='class feature')
f379 = Feature(code='cf43brd15',level=10,name='magical secrets',description='By 10th level, you have plundered magical knowledge from a wide spectrum of disciplines. Choose two spells from any class, including this one. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip.\nThe chosen spells count as bard spells for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Bard table.\nYou learn two additional spells from any class at 14th level and again at 18th level.',type='extra spells',category='class feature')
f380 = Feature(code='cf44brd16',level=20,name='superior inspiration',description='At 20th level, when you roll initiative and have no uses of Bardic Inspiration left, you regain one use.',type='miscellaneous',category='class feature')
f381 = Feature(code='cf45brd17',name='equipment',description='[ul](a) a rapier, (b) a longsword, or (c) any simple weapon[/li/](a) a diplomat\'s pack or (b) an entertainer\'s pack[/li/](a) a lute or (b) any other musical instrument[/li/]Leather armor and a dagger[/ul]',type='starting equipment',category='class feature')
f382 = Feature(code='cf46brd18cl1',level=3,name='bonus proficiencies',description='When you join the College of Lore at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with three skills of your choice.',type='proficiency',category='class feature',list_by_category='skill',number_of=3)
f383 = Feature(code='cf47brd19cl2',level=3,name='cutting words',description='Also at 3rd level, you learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling a Bardic Inspiration die and subtracting the number rolled from the creature\'s roll. You can choose to use this feature after the creature makes its roll, but the DM determines whether the attack roll or ability check succeeds or fails, or before the creature deals its damage. The creature is immune if it can\'t hear you or if it\'s immune to being Charmed.',type='miscellaneous',category='class feature')
f384 = Feature(code='cf48brd20cl3',level=6,name='additional magical secrets',description='At 6th level, you learn two spells of your choice from any class. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast as shown on the Bard table or cantrip. The chosen spells count as bard spells for you but don\'t count against the number of bard spells you know.',type='extra spells',category='class feature')
f385 = Feature(code='cf49brd21cl4',level=14,name='peerless skill',description='Starting at 14th level, when you make an ability check, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to your ability check. You can choose to do so after you roll the die for the ability check, but before the DM tells you whether you succeed or fail.',type='enhanced abilities',category='class feature')
f386 = Feature(code='cf50brd22cv1',level=3,name='bonus proficiencies',description='When you join the College of Valor at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons.',type='proficiency',category='class feature',list_by_category='armor, medium|shield|melee, martial|ranged, martial')
f387 = Feature(code='cf51brd23cv2',level=3,name='combat inspiration',description='Also at 3rd level, you learn to inspire others in battle. A creature that has a Bardic Inspiration die from you can roll that die and add the number rolled to a weapon damage roll it just made. Alternatively, when an attack roll is made against the creature, it can use its reaction to roll the Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to its AC against that attack, after seeing the roll but before knowing whether it hits or misses.',type='enhanced damage',category='class feature')
f388 = Feature(code='cf52brd24cv3',level=6,name='extra attack',description='Starting at 6th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.',type='enhanced damage',category='class feature')
f389 = Feature(code='cf53brd25cv4',level=14,name='battle magic',description='At 14th level, you have mastered the art of weaving spellcasting and weapon use into a single harmonious act. When you use your action to cast a bard spell, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action.',type='enhanced damage',category='class feature')
